    "Table 3: Among the most distinctive LIWC features based on gender, first-generation status, and EC (using a median split to create a low and high EC group), for both the public and private applicants, we present the proportions of features that are the most aligned between the AI-generated essays and each respective subgroup.",
    "For example, among the 29 LIWC features for which the distributions were significantly different in essays written by men versus women applicants, the feature distributions of the AIgenerated essays were closer to those of male applicants for at least 65.5% of features (GPT-4; Private applicants) and up to 79.3% of features (GPT-4; Public applicants).",
    "We next describe our other sociodemographic analyses.",
